<br>
The prisons and court system is so over-crowded they had to come up with plea bargain process and time off for good behavior. This leads to violent criminals being able to walk the streets so we can jail some guy who sold some weed to an adult who chose to  buy it.<br>
<br>
If they bust a hooker, her pimp or someone bails her out, she does no real jail time. BUT it takes quite a bit of our tax dollars to chase this down, takes a cop off the street so he can process the paperwork when maybe he could be of more assistance to the woman getting raped in the parking lot. Or the guy getting his vehicle car-jacked at gun point, or the 7-11 clerk being held up, or the guy getting mugged for his wallet etc.<br>
<br>
Someone brought up health insurance for the regulated hookers. To be honest, if it was regulated THEY would pay their own insurance, like a real job. As it stands now they qualify for medicaid as they have no income on paper. So the way it is now WE PAY for their health insurance. In fact they qualify for welfare and food stamps also. I would rather they pay taxes.<br>
<br>
As for adultry, of course adultry is wrong BUT it goes on. It's the reality, does the wife of the adulterer deserve hiv or herpes etc cause she wasnt aware her husband was cheating?<br>
<br>
The DEA wont be out of a job or useless if drugs became legal, there is still enough crime out there to chase down. The vice squad wont go out of business either, they can certainly track down anyone not following the regulations and anyone participating in the sale of underage girls. Sex crimes will continue to exist and I would rather they spend their time on children who are being sexually abused, women and men who are raped etc.<br>
<br>
Chasing down drug dealers and prostitutes is making us less effective in dealing with other issues that are more of a danger to us over-all. We are clogging up the system with this. <br>
<br>
Originally I felt the guy who is locally trying to start a movement to make those activities legal had some good points, but I thought maybe there was some things I hadnt thought of. On this thread I saw more good points in favor of legalizing these activities.<br>
<br>
What I saw against it, was that people feel these things are morally wrong. I dont believe you can legislate morals, my morals and someone elses may clash. I have yet to hear one good argument for keeping weed illegal for sure. Any argument against legalizing weed means you need to rally to illegalize alcohol and tabacco also. To be honest this goes for the rest of the drugs too. Alcohol and tabacco are addictive, they do harm others around you. Why are those things legal and the rest arent? Makes no sense to me.<br>
<br>
To those who feel they should remain illegal, you prove the point that making them legal dosent mean you will participate in these activities. Just because its legal dosent mean people will do it, just because its illegal dosent mean people will refrain either. So why are we spending so much in taxes to track this down and fight this losing battle based on morality? Thought church and state were separate. Maybe they arent as separate as we think. <p><center><img src="http://www.danos.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/jellah.gif" width="577" height="162"></center></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showPrevMessage?topicID=1725.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showNextMessage?topicID=1725.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1725.topic&index=51><img src=http://www.unbeliever.net/images/lanys/postreply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.emailToFriend?topicID=1725.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.threadControl?topicID=1725.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1725.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingis